cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with adversarial training for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a "gambler" network, which is a form of reinforcement learning (cs.LG) and the paper also discusses the use of uncertainty in the segmentation process, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for describing the proposed method (cs.CL) and the use of neural networks for training (cs.NE).
